      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The yellowing leaves on your blueberry bushes could be related to iron deficiency. Iron is essential for photosynthesis and nutrient uptake. When the pH level of the soil drops below 4.0, it can become \"acidic,\" making it difficult for the plant to absorb iron. Most blueberry bushes prefer acidic soil with a pH between 4.0 and 5.5, as these nuts require adequate iron levels; its absorption is greatly reduced with very low or high pH levels.",
